'''Dan Costello Sr''' was a pioneer of [[tourism]] in [[Fiji]]. He died in the Gold Coast in [[Queensland, Australia]] in February 2010. He was one of the Pacific's major tourism pioneers and launched the Beachcomber Resort and Beachcomber Cruises back in the 1950s. He was a father of seven children and one of them was musician [[Daniel Rae Costello]].<ref>Heral Sun [http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/breaking-news/fiji-tourist-pioneer-dan-costello-dies/story-e6frf7jx-1225829347574 Fiji tourist industry pioneer Dan Costello dies]</ref>

