{{notability|Academics|date=January 2011}}
'''Stanley J. Shapiro''' (born 1934) is Professor Emeritus of Marketing at [[Simon Fraser University]], [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]]. He has served as dean of [[McGill University]]'s School of Management (1973&ndash;1979) and dean of Business Administration (1987&ndash;1997) for Simon Fraser University.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.archives.mcgill.ca/resources/guide/vol1/rg28.htm|title=Management|publisher=[[McGill University]]|accessdate=2011-01-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://business.nmsu.edu/~mhyman/M670_Articles/Shapiro_JPPM_2005.pdf|title=Looking Backward—and Ahead|publisher=Journal of Public Policy & Marketing via [[New Mexico State University]] College of Business|accessdate=2011-01-23}}</ref> Shapiro published many books in areas ranging from marketing history to the financial dimensions of marketing management. Prior to joining Simon Fraser University, Dr. Shapiro was a Professor of Marketing (1967&ndash;1980), and he had earlier taught at the Wharton School for three years before entering industry. Dr. Shapiro has also been a Visiting Professor at Queen’s University, Bentley College and Royal Roads University. After retirement, he taught one of the first entirely “online” MBA I level marketing courses.<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography|url=http://www.acsenda.com/about-us/academic-council/stanley-j-shapiro-ba-mba-ph-d-external-academic/|accessdate=2 February 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203203754/http://www.acsenda.com/about-us/academic-council/stanley-j-shapiro-ba-mba-ph-d-external-academic/|archivedate=3 February 2014|df=}}</ref> * B.A., [[Harvard College]] * MBA, PhD, [[Wharton Business School]], [[University of Pennsylvania]]. ** Doctoral thesis on the politics of distribution' study focusing on the Ontario Hog Producers
==Academic career== * Wharton Business School * McGill Graduate School of Business (1967&ndash;1981) * Simon Fraser University (1981&ndash;1999)
